<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Calls for World Free From Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina Saturday called for global efforts to free the world from
the threats of all categories of arms.
</P>
<P>
"Let peace and development be our agenda for the new century,"
Hasina said in a message on the occasion of the Hiroshima Day.
</P>
<P>
She also called for taking a renewed pledge on this day to
engage all efforts of mankind toward preserving the human race
with its rich diversity.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister reiterated Bangladesh's unequivocal
commitment to free the world from all weapons of mass destruction,
especially the nuclear weapons for the cause of world peace and
security.
</P>
<P>
Referring to meaningful pledges made by the international
community toward durable peace since the Hiroshima incident,
Hasina said the international community achieved much in its
efforts to rid the world of chemical, biological and inhumane
weapons.
</P>
<P>
But, she added, the huge stockpile of nuclear arsenals at the
advent of the 21st century remained as a stark reminder of horrors
of Hiroshima and the single most threat to the existence of
mankind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
