<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak reshuffled his
cabinet Sunday morning, naming four of his ministers to hold
concurrent posts.
</P>
<P>
At Sunday morning's weekly cabinet meeting, Communications
Minister Binyamin Ben Eliezer took up the Construction and Housing
Minister post, while Minister in Prime Minister's Office Haim
Ramon also got an additional portfolio of Interior Minister.
</P>
<P>
Both of them had been ministers in their respective new posts
in the previous government, according to a cabinet statement
issued by Barak's Office.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it was announced that Justice Minister Yossi Beilin
would also head the Religious Affairs Ministry, and Finance
Minister Avraham Shochat would act as National Infrastructure
Minister concurrently. (Israel-Cabinet Reshuffle)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Two women were killed and three passers-by were
injured in a premeditated blast in the Russian Dagestani district
capital of Khasavyurt on Sunday, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
An investigation shows the explosion was caused by a bomb
planted in a Moskvich (Muscovites) automobile parked near a local
service center, killing the two women in the car and badly
damaging the local library and community center, Interfax quoted
the city police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The police and the Federal Security Service officers have
sealed off the blast site of blast, and an investigation is
underway. Dagestani Interior Minister Adilgerei Magomedtagirov
has left for Khasavyurt to find out the motive of the explosion.
(Russia-Dagestan-Explosion)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Naval units of Iran's army Sunday in the Iranian
territorial waters in the Persian Gulf intercepted a ship carrying
800 tons of contraband Iraqi oil.
</P>
<P>
The ship, registered in Belize, capital of Honduras, has been
escorted to an Iranian port, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Iraq, under U.N. sanctions since its 1990 invasion of Kuwait,
has to sell oil under a U.N. supervision system, but smugglers
tend to ship oil from the country for huge profits.
</P>
<P>
In April and May, the Iranian elite Islamic Revolutionary
Guards Corps in Iranian territorial waters intercepted some 13 oil
tankers smuggling oil from Iraq. (Iran-Iraq-Ship)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Deposed Fiji Prime Minister Mahendra Chaudhry, who
was released last month after being held hostage for eight weeks
by rebel leader George Speight, will visit India on August 17,
Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"We will give him a hearty welcome," Vajpayee said at a
function here.
</P>
<P>
India greeted with a sense of relief the decision of Fiji's
Great Council of Chiefs to release Chaudhry and his cabinet
colleagues from detention in Fiji's parliament building where they
were taken hostage on May 19.
</P>
<P>
New Delhi hoped that this first step would lead to the
restoration of a democratic and constitutional government within
the framework of the Fijian Constitution of 1997. (India-Fiji-
Visit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
