<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua)-- Following are highlights of major
diplomatic news stories released today by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
Cambodian King, Queen Arrive in Beijing
</P>
<P>
Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk and Queen Norodom Monique
Sihanouk arrived here this afternoon for a routine checkup and
recuperation.
</P>
<P>
The king and the queen were greeted at the airport by Chinese
Vice-Foreign Minister Yang Wenchang and other officials.
</P>
<P>
NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Kiribati Parliament Leader
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zhenghua, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), met today with Tekiree Tamuera,
speaker of Kiribati's House of Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that bilateral relations have been developing
steadily since the two countries established diplomatic relations
in 1980, and leaders of the two countries have had frequent
exchanges of visits, and the two parliaments have also had
increased exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Jiang appreciated Kiribati's consistent adherence to the one-
China policy.
</P>
<P>
NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Thai Delegation
</P>
<P>
Buhe, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC), met today with Thai Deputy Prime Minister
Korn Dabbaransi and his delegation.
</P>
<P>
Dabbaransi is leading a delegation of Thai businessmen and
artists in China to mark the 25th anniversary of the forging of
Sino-Thai diplomatic relations, at the invitation of the Chinese
People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC)
.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Buhe said that the two countries have had
frequent high-level exchanges of visits in recent years, and
bilateral cooperation has been fruitful, and Sino-Thai relations
can serve as a good model for promoting good-neighborly relations
and cooperation between nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
