<HEADLINE> Chechen Rebels Shoot Down Russian Helicopter in Ingushetia Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A Russian military helicopter was
shot down by Chechen rebels over the Russian Ingushetia republic's
territory near the Chechen-Ingush border Sunday, Russian news
agencies reported.
</P>
<P>
The Mi-8 helicopter made an emergency landing near the village
of Arshty, east Ingushetia, after coming under rebels' fire from
light arms during take-off on Sunday morning, the Interfax news
agency cited the headquarters of the Russian combined forces in
the North Caucasus as saying.
</P>
<P>
One serviceman on board the aircraft suffered serious injuries
and was taken to hospital. The others in the helicopter remain
unharmed, the Itar-Tass news agency quoted the headquarters as
saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
