<HEADLINE> 25th Harbin Summer Music Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The 25th Harbin Summer Music
Festival opened here today in this capital of northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province, with the presence of more than 20 art
troupes from all over the country.
</P>
<P>
The festival has been jointly organized by the Ministry of
Culture and the government of Harbin City since 1961.
</P>
<P>
During the 10-day festival, more than 30 concerts and dance and
drama shows will be presented, including art performances by
American and Japanese musicians and singers from Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Harbin has become one of the major concert centers in China.
From May this year, more than 150 art performances by Harbin
citizens have been shown in squares in the city, entertaining
three million local people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
