because they have more close relations with Peres, former Israeli
prime minister and a Nobel Peace Laureate for his peace efforts to
masterplan the Israeli-Palestinian Oslo accords in early 1990s.
They also worry a right-wing president will tamper with Israeli
Prime Minister Ehud Barak's peace efforts. 
