<HEADLINE> Pakistani Seafood Exports Reach US$130.9 million Yearly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's fish and shrimp
exports have been increasing steadily to reach 130.9 million U.S.
dollars yearly, the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The country's total exports are 8.4 billion dollars yearly and
seafood figures eighth on the export list.
</P>
<P>
However, the APP report said, Only 13 percent of the 700,000
tons of fish and shrimps caught every year are exported and
consumed in 43 countries. In addition 10 percent of the catch is
dried and exported to Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's coastal line is 1,120 kilometers long, 30 percent of
which is in Sindh and 70 percent in Balochistan.
</P>
<P>
The value-added exports have become essential to fully
utilizing the sea resources, keeping in view the international
standard and costs, the APP report said. It added that substantial
foreign exchange can be earned through processing of seafood
besides a manifold increase in exports.
</P>
