<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Eradicate Polio by End of 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan, with the efforts and
cooperation of every citizen, can completely eradicate polio by
the end of 2000, according to a World Health Organization(WHO)
report available here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The number of polio cases in Pakistan has dropped dramatically
in recent years and there is a very good chance of completely
stopping transmission of the disease in this country by the end of
this year, WHO Medical Officer Anthony Mounts said.
</P>
<P>
According to a study conducted by Mounts, the vaccination teams
throughout Pakistan have been working very hard under difficult
conditions to see that vaccine is delivered to every child in the
country during polio campaigns.
</P>
<P>
He urged the people to get their children vaccinated during
vaccination campaigns in their areas. 
