<HEADLINE> International Seminar on Northeast Asia Peace Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The ninth international seminar
on regional peace and development in northeast Asia came to a
close today in this capital of northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 specialists, entrepreneurs and government
officials from Japan, the Republic of Korea (ROK), Russia,
Mongolia and China attended the two-day seminar, with regional
economic cooperation modes in northeast Asia in the 21st century
as the theme.
</P>
<P>
The participants presented more than 70 academic papers at the
seminar, which was organized by the Northeast Asian Studies Center
and Northeast Asia Academy of Jilin University.
</P>
<P>
They also held discussions and exchanges on subjects including
the present situation and prospects of economic cooperation in
northeast Asia, population, resources and the environment,
development and cooperation in tourism, economic development and
cooperation in the Tumen River area, and international relations
and regional peace in northeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The participants agreed that, along with expansion in economic
globalization, the major favorable turn in peace and development
on the Korean Peninsula, and economic recovery in northeast Asia,
the seminar would help expand research on northeast Asia, and
would also have a big impact on the promotion of economic
cooperation in this region.
</P>
<P>
"Northeast Asia will be one of the world's most active regions
in terms of economic and political cooperation in the 21st century,
" said Kan Yanhe, of the Chinese Education Ministry.
</P>
<P>
He added that China's active participation in economic
cooperation in northeast Asia is of great significance for winning
China a peaceful international environment and speeding up its
modernization. 
