<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Hits Japan's Ogasawara Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A powerful earthquake measuring 7.3
on the open-ended Richter scale rocked Ogasawara Islands south of
Tokyo on Sunday afternoon, jolting large areas in eastern and
northeastern Japan, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage or injuries and no
tsunami or tidal wave warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which struck at 4:28 p.m. (local time), was also
felt in downtown Tokyo and parts of Chiba, Fukushima, Ibaraki,
Kanagawa Fukushima, Saitama, Tochigi and Yamagata prefectures.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was about 430 kilometers under the
sea off the uninhabited isle of Torishima, about 600 km south of
Tokyo, the agency said. 
