<HEADLINE> Pippig Cleared of Doping Suspicions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- German marathon runner Uta Pippig,
banned for the past two years after turning in a positive test,
has been cleared of all suspicion of drug taking, the president of
the German Athletics Federation Helmut Digel announced on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pippig, the 33-year-old runner who now lives in the United
States, was banned after testing positive to a high level of
testosterone during a training session at Boulder, Colorado, on
April 23, 1998.
</P>
