</P>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- United Airlines, the world's largest carrier,
canceled more than 150 flights at Chicago's O'Hare International
Airport on Saturday because of crew shortages and bad weather, the
company said.
</P>
<P>
United pilots have refused to work overtime since their
contract expired in April, said United Airlines spokesman Chris
Brathwaite. The company and the pilots' union are negotiating a
contract with a federal mediator and hope to have a new agreement
in place by early September. (United -Airlines-Flights)
</P>
