<HEADLINE> SAARC Summit Likely to Be Held in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The postponed summit of the South
Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) is expected to
be held in December, The Independent newspaper said Sunday quoting
diplomatic sources.
</P>
<P>
The 13th conference of the heads of state and government of the
SAARC countries, scheduled to be held in Kathmandu in November,
1999, was postponed as India refused to attend following the
military takeover in Pakistan in last October.
</P>
<P>
Despite the sudden setback in holding the summit, host Nepal
has been in constant touch with the six other member countries to
reschedule the programs of the SAARC conference through mutual
consultations, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Technical committees of the association at various levels have
also been working with a view to creating a conductive atmosphere
for holding the summit.
</P>
<P>
Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee and Pakistan's Chief
Executive, General Pervez Musharraf are expected to meet in New
York in September, in the sidelines of the United Nations
Millennium Summit.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic circles hoped that after a direct contact between
Vajpayee and Musharraf, a positive ground will be prepared for
holding the SAARC summit by the end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
