<HEADLINE> Venus Williams Reaches Acura Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Venus Williams eliminated Amy
Frazier 6-2, 6-3 to reach the final of the 535,000 US dollars
Acura Classic tennis tournament in Carlsbad, California on
Saturday, claiming her 14th straight match victory.
</P>
<P>
The third-ranked Williams thus will go after her third
tournament title in a row in Sunday's final against the winner of
either Anna Kournikova and Monica Seles.
</P>
<P>
Frazier, who upset top-ranked Martina Hingis in the
quarterfinals, lamented that "she hit the ball so hard, I was just
trying to stay in the points and she really wasn't letting me do
anything."
</P>
<P>
Frazier was barely competitive on a day when Williams had a sub-
par performance by committing 28 unforced errors. "I didn't play
too well, I felt I was off-balance quite a lot," said Williams.
</P>
<P>
Frazier picked up early service breaks in both sets. But in the
first, Williams reeled off the last five games to close the set,
and erased a 2-0 deficit in the second set to close out the match
in one hour six minutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
