<HEADLINE> Levy Enters First Career Final at Masters Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Qualifier Harel Levy of Israel
fought into his first career ATP final, upsetting Czech Jiri Novak
6-3, 1-6, 6-4 in the semifinal here Saturday at the Tennis Masters
Series-Canada in Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Levy will face Russian Marat Safin in Sunday's final, The
Russian eighth-seeded entered the final by defeated South African
Wayne Ferreira 6-2, 5-7, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Levy, playing in his first Masters Series event,
won the first five games of the match, then broke Novak for the
fourth time in the ninth game to claim the first set, but Novak
rallied to win the second in 25 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Levy, the first qualifier finalist here since Anders Jarryd in
1983, broke Novak in the ninth game of set three to give himself a
chance to be the first Israeli to win an ATP title since Amos
Mansdorf won at Washington in 1993. 
</P>
