<HEADLINE> Thai PM: Thailand to Stand with Peace Lovers Worldwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Thai people and government
will stand by the side of Hiroshima citizens and peace lovers
worldwide to promote and create lasting peace and harmony among
humanity, the Thai News Agency (TNA) Sunday quoted Thai Prime
Minister Chuan Leekpai as saying.
</P>
<P>
In his message on Saturday to Mayor of Hiroshima to commemorate
the devastating nuclear bombardment of Hiroshima by the Allied
Group on August 6, 1945, days before the end of the World War II,
Chuan said that the August 6 incident is significant not only for
Hiroshima people, but also for all the humanity.
</P>
<P>
Thailand had seen the importance of continued attempts to
promote a common stance on peace in the international community,
and was determined to continue to adhere to its position on
supporting for confidence building up and creation of
understanding in the Southeast Asian region, which will lead to
sustainable peace and stability in the 21st century, based on
lessons from the incident in Hiroshima, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Thai people and government would stand by the side of
Hiroshima citizens and peace lovers worldwide to create lasting
peace and harmony among humanity, pledged the Thai leader.
</P>
</TEXT>
