<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in northwest China has over
the past few years confiscated and destroyed some 300,000 maps
containing errors. The errors include wrong border lines between
China and neighboring countries and wrong boundary lines between
Chinese provinces and autonomous regions, missing important
islands, as well as marking place names in wrong locations.
</P>
<P>
A Boeing 767-400ER airplane, the newest member in the 767 fleet,
landed on August 2 at Urumqi, capital of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region in northwest China, with more than 40 passengers on an
around-the-world tour that will take the plane to 17 cities and
four continents.
</P>
<P>
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region has decided to select
eight bureau-level officials through competitive examinations,
with half of the positions destined for ethnic minority candidates.
This is the first time Xinjiang introduces competitive
examinations to replace the time-honored practice of appointing
officials by higher authorities.
</P>
<P>
TIBET: Mt. Kangrinboqe and L. Mapan Yumco, worshipped as the
holy mountain and sacred lake by Tibetans, have become new tourist
attractions in recent years. Tibet has opened two specially
designed tourist routes to the holy mountain and sacred lake.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of ducks and gulls have returned to the Lhalu
Wetland in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region as ecological
environment has been greatly improved in recent years. The wetland
covers 6.2 square kilometers meters and is considered as the
largest wetland in China's urban districts.
</P>
<P>
SICHUAN: Sichuan Airlines based in Chengdu, capital of
southwest Sichuan province, has recently put MA60, China's brand-
new regional aircraft into use. The Xi'an Aircraft Industry
Corporation, the plane's producer, has received orders for 10
MA60s from several domestic airlines including Sichuan Airlines.
</P>
<P>
GUANGXI: A 178-meter-high dam has been completed at the
Tianshengqiao hydropower station in south Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region recently. The dam was built with 18 million
cubic meters of stone and earth.
</P>
<P>
HAINAN: China will build its largest flour mill in Yangpu in
the island province of Hainan. The preparatory work is underway
and the construction is expected to start before the end of the
year. The mill is designed to have an annual processing capacity
of 500,000 tons of imported wheat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
