<HEADLINE> Over 10 Million Tanzanian Voters to be Registered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Over 10 million Tanzanians
are expected to be registered for the forthcoming general
elections during voter registration exercise which will start
throughout the country on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The National Electoral Commission (NEC) Chairman Judge Lewis
Makame said here on Monday that the exercise, which is expected to
last for about three weeks, will be carried out in 32,200
registration centers in the country's 231 constituencies.
</P>
<P>
Each center will have one registration assistant and that all
the 13 fully registered political parties are allowed to place
agents to make a close follow-up on the exercise, the chairman
told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
"It is our hope that the agents would work hand in hand with
the commission in making the exercise a success," said Makame,
adding that the NEC is optimistic that the registration will be
carried out smoothly as it was the case in 1995, when Tanzania
held its first multi-party general elections and some 8.9 million
voters were registered.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a continuous exercise, no weekends, no public
holidays," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Election campaigns will take place between August 19 and
October 28. All the 13 fully registered political parties in
Tanzania will participate in the second multi-party presidential,
parliamentary and councilor elections to be held on October 29.
</P>
</TEXT>
