<HEADLINE> Guinea-Bissau, Senegal Sign Accord to Re-open Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Senegal and Guinea-Bissau have
signed an agreement on the immediate re-opening of the two
countries' common border closed since mid-July,  the Angolan
official news agency Angop reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The accord was concluded in Salikenie, a Senegalese locality
nearest to the Guinea-Bissau frontier, after negotiations between
Senegalese Interior Minister Mamadou Niang and Guinea-Bissau's
Foreign Minister Iaia Djalo.
</P>
<P>
Accusing the armed bandits from Guinea-Bissau of robbing and
plundering in the Senegalese cities, Senegalese residents living
along the frontier blocked the border areas with Guinea-Bissau.
</P>
<P>
The two countries later created a joint commission for
investigating, identifying and restituting the robbed goods of the
Senegalese residents.
</P>
<P>
In the agreement, the two sides promised to assure a "better
security along the frontier for impeding the incursion of armed
bandits". 
</P>
