<HEADLINE> Heavy Fighting Erupts in Central Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government troops and
the armed rebels led by Jonas Savimbi entered into heavy fighting
at the weekend for the control of Gamba, a strategic point in the
Angolan central highland, the Angolan News Agency (Angop) reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The fighting began earlier last week when the rebels tried to
overrun Gamba, located some 40 kilometers southeast of the town of
Nharea in northwestern Bie Province. But the report did not
mention any casualties suffered so far by either side.
</P>
<P>
Gamba is considered a key point for the stabilization of the
military situation in Bie, where the long-standing rebel
strongholds of Andulo and Nharea were captured by government
forces last autumn.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the rebels staged the fighting to ease
pressure on its forces in central and southern Bie, where the
government has allegedly launched a major offensive against the
rebels.
</P>
<P>
Unconfirmed reports indicated that Jonas Savimbi, leader of the
rebel National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA),
may have installed the rebel military command in southern Bie near
the border with Cuando Cubango Province. 
</P>
