<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican Law Professor to Head UN Office in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican law professor Mussagy
Jeichande will be appointed as Chief of the United Nations Office
to Angola (UNOA), said reports reaching here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statement was made by the UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan
in his letter to members of the Security Council, which said that
Jeichande will act as his representative and head of the UNOA.
</P>
<P>
Mussagy Jeichande, 51, is a law lecturer at the Maputo
Institute of Applied Science and Technology.
</P>
<P>
In October 1999, the UN opened the 30-member UN Office to
Angola, with an aim to follow the development of the humanitarian,
social-economic and political-military situation in the country
which has been suffering some 26 years of civil war. 
</P>
