<HEADLINE> Zambia's Coffee Output to Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia Coffee Board (ZCB)
expected the country's coffee output to quadruple in the next five
years, which is to earn at least 25 million U.S. dollars, Times of
Zambia reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The plantation target by 2005/2006 will be 3,500 hectares while
output should reach 10,000 tons with expected earnings at 25
million dollars, said Joseph Wanga, ZCB's extension services
manager.
</P>
<P>
Although Zambia is a small producer of coffee in the region, it
will be geared to improve and compete favorably if more farmers
are encouraged, the manager said.
</P>
<P>
Zambia produced 2,179 tons of coffee in the 1999/2000 season
with a total earning of 4.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
There are 65 large-scale coffee growers and 800 small-scale
ones in the country. 
