<HEADLINE> Zambia to Earn $65 Million From Flower Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Zambia Export Growers Association
(ZEGA) is expected to earn 65 million U.S. dollars from flower and
vegetable exports to Europe for the 2000/2001 season, Times of
Zambia newspaper reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Zambian flower growers enjoy production costs that are 50
percent less than those of the producers in the Netherlands, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Last year ZEGA exported over 8,000 tons of roses and summer
flowers with an export value of 62.6 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Netherlands Management Cooperation program consultant Hans
Ekelmans was quoted as saying here Sunday that "Zambia should be
more aggressive because the country has a good future".
</P>
<P>
The floriculture sector has made significant contributions to
Zambia's hard currency earnings and has created 12,000 jobs. About
94 percent of Zambia's flower output has been auctioned in the
Netherlands. 
</P>
