<HEADLINE> Kenya to Host Global Health Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Kenya will host the global
reproductive health conference, the first of its kind in Africa,
at the Safari Park Hotel in its capital Nairobi from August 13 to
18.
</P>
<P>
Under the theme "Lessons Learned in Reproductive Health", the
meeting, sponsored by the Plan International, will draw over 100
leading world health professionals and heads of non-governmental-
organizations dealing with reproductive health care programs in
Africa, Asia and Latin America, the People daily reported on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The six-day meeting will feature prominently on such issues as
poverty and HIV/AIDS pandemic, which have undermined the progress
made in the health sector like safe motherhood.
</P>
<P>
The professionals will look at issues such as innovative
programs in family planning and child spacing and how to integrate
these into other health or related development programs as well as
reviewing child survival programs. 
</P>
