<HEADLINE> Girl Killed in Riot in Uganda  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A three-year-old girl was killed
when anti-riot police battled a mob in the northern Ugandan town
of Lira, the New Vision newspaper reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The police opened fire on the crowd, killing three-year old
Brenda Acan instantly when civilians attacked and burnt a police
station to protest the murder of a local businessman who was
gunned down by unknown gunmen in the town on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The mob who had wanted to lynch suspected robbers set ablaze
the police outpost and smashed a civilian vehicle belonging to the
traffic police chief.
</P>
<P>
A suspect was grabbed from the police during the riot and was
beaten to death by the angry mob, it said.
</P>
<P>
Some policemen were critically injured by stray stones and were
admitted to Lira Hospital together with a man and a woman who were
also shot.
</P>
<P>
Other suspects were saved by a reinforcement of the anti-riot
police who used tear gas to cordon off the scene. 
