<HEADLINE> Kaunda Urges SADC to Fight Against AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The AIDS pandemic is causing
worse devastation in Africa than the slave trade in the history,
former Zambian President Kenneth Kaunda told Southern African
Development Community (SADC) leaders on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing SADC heads of state in a closed-door session in
Windhoek, Namibia, Kaunda said the regional body should show the
same commitment to fighting the disease as displayed by anti-
slavery activists.
</P>
<P>
"We should not be afraid to talk about it," said Kaunda.
</P>
